Class Supervisor

java.lang.Object
models.User
models.Supervisor
Direct Known Subclasses:
Coordinator
public class Supervisor extends User
This class is a supervisor which is a subclass of the user. Supervisor inherits attributes and methods from the user class. A supervisor is able to access the FYP management system.
Version:
1.0
Author:
Dennis

  • Constructor Details

    • Supervisor

      public Supervisor(String userName, String email, String password)
      This constructs a student with a specificed username, email, password. The username, email and password will be feed into the super class which is user. Afterwards, we will attain all the project that have the supervisor is part based on his username through the use of another class method and put it in the supervisor's project list. Then we will initialise the attribute supervisingProjectCount with a method used on this project list.
      Parameters:
      userName - the username of the supervisor
      email - the email of the supervisor
      password - the password of the supervisor

  • Method Details

    • checkAndSetProjectStatus

      public void checkAndSetProjectStatus()
      This method will run through the supervisor's list of project and checks for the number of project that he is currently supervising. This means any project with a status of reserved or allocated. If the number of projects that he is supervising is less than 2, we will check for any projects in this list of project that have the status unavailable and set the project status as available. If the number of projects that he is supervising is 2, we will check for any project in this list of project that have the status available and set the project status as unavailable.

    • checkNumSupervisingProject

      public int checkNumSupervisingProject()
      This method will run through the supervisor's list of project and checks for the total number of project that he is currently supervising. This means any project with a status of reserved or allocated project.
      Returns:
      the total number of project that supervisor is supervising.

    • getSupervisingProjectCount

      public int getSupervisingProjectCount()
      This method gets the current number of project the supervisor is supervising. Meaning the total number of projects with the status of allocated or reserved.
      Returns:
      the total number of project that supervisor is supervising.

    • getProject

      public Project getProject(int projectID)
      Thie methods get the project that is in the supervisor's project list based on what is the project id inputted. If such a project id is not found in the supervisor's project list, it will get nothing.
      Parameters:

      Returns:
      the project object of the specificed project id.

    • getAllocatedProject

      public Project getAllocatedProject(int projectID)
      Thie methods get the allocated project that is in the supervisor's project list based on what is the project id inputted. If such a project id is not found in the supervisor's project list, it will get nothing. If such a project id is found, but the project status is not allocated, it will also get nothing.
      Parameters:
      projectID - This is the value of the project id that you want to get back.
      Returns:
      the allocated project object of the specificed project id.

    • getAllocatedProjectList

      public List<Project> getAllocatedProjectList()
      This method get all the project that have the status allocated in the supervisor's project list. This method will run through all the project in supervisor's project list, if the project is allocated, it will be appeneded into a new list of project.
      Returns:
      the supervisor's list of allocated projects.
